gmd:title.gco:CharacterString: Bureau of Motor Vehicle License Branch Locations: Indiana, 2007

gmd:organisationName.gco:CharacterString: Indiana Bureau of Motor Vehicles (BMV) (Data source)

gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: BMV_LICENSE_BRANCHES_IN is a point shapefile showing the locations of 142 branch offices of the Indiana Bureau of Motor Vehicles (BMV). Addresses for each branch office were obtained on March 22, 2007, from the Web site of the BMV (http://www.in.gov/bmv/branches/). A shapefile was created using the Geocoding tool in ESRI ArcMap 9.2 and street information licensed from Tele Atlas, Dynamap 2000 v. 17.0.

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: This data set was compiled to create a statewide GIS layer showing locations of BMV license branches in Indiana.

gmd:credit.gco:CharacterString: Data is from Indiana Bureau of Motor Vehicles

gmd:measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: No checks for logical consistency were made.
All branch offices listed by the Indiana Bureau of Motor Vehicles have been included.

Street addresses for branch office locations were obtained from the Web site of the Indiana Bureau of Motor Vehicles and are assumed to be accurate. Automated geocoding produced match scores of 100 percent for 111 offices and match scores of 81 to 96 percent for 16 offices. Nine locations were re-matched to produce scores ranging from 32 to 76 percent. Six locations could not be matched (match score equals zero); the locations of these offices were determined by using MapQuest (http://www.mapquest.com/maps/) or by plotting the nearest town center.
For match scores greater than 80 percent, plotted locations are generally within a few hundred feet of actual locations. For match scores less than 80 percent, horizontal accuracy is unknown.
The vertical positional accuracy was not a factor in the production of this shapefile.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Web-site URLs and addresses for each license branch were compiled by personnel of the Indiana Geological Survey (IGS) from the Indiana Bureau of Motor Vehicles (BMV), Branch Locator (http://www.in.gov/bmv/branches/). The BMV address list was savee as a Microsoft Excel spreadsheet named "BMV_LOCATIONS.XLS."

IGS personnel used street information licensed from Tele Atlas in ESRI ArcMap 9.2 to build an "Address Locator." Using the "Geocoding" tool to perform address matching, locations contained in BMV_LOCATIONS.XLS were address-matched. All 136 branch locations were matched to known addresses. Six locations needed to be plotted manually, either by using locations plotted by MapQuest or using the nearest town center. The output was saved as BMV_LICENSE_BRANCHES_IN.SHP. The following fields were then deleted from the attribute table: "Side," "ARC_Street," "ARC_Zone," "Address2," and "State."

This metadata file was pre-parsed and parsed using CNS (Chew and Spit, v. 2.6.1) and MP (Metadata Parser, v. 2.7.1) software written by Peter N. Schweitzer (U.S. Geological Survey). The errors generated by MP were all addressed and corrected, except that no values were assigned to "Abscissa_Resolution" and "Ordinate_Resolution."
